OK, I want to make one thing abundantly clear.
We performed this demonstration at

00:07:57.700 --> 00:08:01.360
25,000 feet [7,500m]. I had about three to five minutes of consciousness left.

00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:05.040
However, most airliners travel at 35,000 feet [10,000m].

00:08:05.040 --> 00:08:08.400
Look at this chart: There is way less oxygen up there.

00:08:08.420 --> 00:08:13.660
At 35,000 feet [10,000m] you literally have seconds
of useful consciousness at that altitude.

00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:17.290
You can go from a normally rational
person to someone so helpless you can

00:08:17.290 --> 00:08:19.850
even save yourself if your life depends
on it.

00:08:20.340 --> 00:08:21.400
I don’t-

00:08:22.260 --> 00:08:23.770
I don’t wanna die

00:08:30.400 --> 00:08:33.700
